	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Heh, I played with this over the weekend some, for fun.<br />
<br />
I noticed that yes, I was easily able to recreate this effect over and over.  If I have enough mana by a bit to cast say, a spark, but not a lot of extra, it would tell me insufficient mana to cast the spell and my total mana would drop by 1% or something near this.  I was able to do this over and over and over.<br />
<br />
However, I noticed that if I tried to cast, say Ancient Core Fire while only having the mana needed for a spark showing in my mana bar, it would tell me insufficient mana and my mana count did not waver.<br />
<br />
Sounds to me that the poster stumbled upon a bug, OR as someone above mentioned, it is reading these as fizzles for some reason and taking away the minimum mana that a fizzle takes.<br />
<br />
Intersting issue for sure.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
